article.description: — Tyler Polley had 19 points as UConn defeated Butler 72-60 on Saturday.
article.headline: Polley scores 19 to lead UConn over Butler 72-60
article.linkText: Polley scores 19 to lead UConn over Butler 72-60
article.story: INDIANAPOLIS -- — Tyler Polley had 19 points as UConn defeated Butler 72-60 on Saturday. Tyrese Martin had 15 points and seven rebounds for UConn (6-1, 3-1 Big East Conference). Isaiah Whaley added three blocks. R.J. Cole had seven rebounds. Bryce Nze had 18 points for the Bulldogs (3-6, 2-4). Aaron Thompson added 14 points and six assists. Bryce Golden had 10 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
